27/01/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan praised US leadership in the war on terror and promised that his government would remain committed to the effort. During a speech on foreign policy goals Monday (26 January), he also noted Turkey's relations with Israel and reiterated his government's desire to play the role of intermediary in future talks between Israel and Syria. Erdogan also renewed his call for an international conference in Ankara on the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. He is making a six-day visit to the United States, which includes a meeting Wednesday with President George W. Bush. (BBC, Anadolu Agency - 27/01/04; AFP - 26/01/04)
